    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Louis A. Cornelius was a Grand Rapids businessman, president of the Wolverine Brass Works. In addition, he was an active Freemason. During the depression, he was director of the Grand Rapids Welfare Union.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection consists of photocopies of letters exchanged with Michigan Senator Arthur H. Vandenberg, 1927-1951, and four scrapbooks, 1910-1933, concerning his business and Masonic activities and his chairmanship of Grand Rapids Welfare Union fund-raising drive during the depression.</p>
    </scopecontent>
